            <content:encoded><![CDATA[https://kotaku.com/game-awards-winners-christmas-gifts-astro-bot-1851720506<br/><br/><div id="readability-page-1" class="page"><div><div><figure id="" data-id="b920af9769bcaf1fa7227494e5d2a567" data-recommend-id="image://b920af9769bcaf1fa7227494e5d2a567" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Astro Bot, Metaphor: ReFantazio and Hellblade II." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Astro Bot, Metaphor: ReFantazio and Hellblade II." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Sony / Ninja Theory / ATLUS / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="b920af9769bcaf1fa7227494e5d2a567" data-recommend-id="image://b920af9769bcaf1fa7227494e5d2a567" data-format="jpg" data-width="1920" data-height="1080" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Astro Bot, Metaphor: ReFantazio and Hellblade II." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/game-awards-2024-rebirth-astro-bot-winners-goty-list-1851720291&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/game-awards-2024-rebirth-astro-bot-winners-goty-list-1851720291">The Game Awards</a></span>, the biggest annual celebration of video games, commenced this past Thursday, handing out awards to the titles that have proven most popular in 2024. There’s a fairly good chance that if you’re fortunate enough to be bought gaming gifts, one of these could be showing up in your stocking. So we’ve pulled together a selection of guides for those award-winning games most likely to appear under your tree this holiday.</p><p>Whether your tastes are action, strategy, sports or teeny cute robots, we’ve got you covered. And if you don’t find your specific game on <em>this</em> list, then chances are we’ve got you covered elsewhere in <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/game-tips?_gl=1*1wlt6bw*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczNDE5MDk1MS40NTMuMS4xNzM0MTkxMTUwLjI4LjAuMA..&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/game-tips?_gl=1*1wlt6bw*_ga*MTk5MTE1MDYyMi4xNzIyNjAzODYw*_ga_V4QNJTT5L0*MTczNDE5MDk1MS40NTMuMS4xNzM0MTkxMTUwLjI4LjAuMA..">our enormous archive of 2024 game guides</a></span>.</p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="b5f280335308fadf0d3dfd73e95c57b6" data-recommend-id="image://b5f280335308fadf0d3dfd73e95c57b6" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="740" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Astro Bot with a dog robot on his back." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Astro Bot with a dog robot on his back." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="false" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Image<!-- -->: <!-- -->Sony</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="b5f280335308fadf0d3dfd73e95c57b6" data-recommend-id="image://b5f280335308fadf0d3dfd73e95c57b6" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="740" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Astro Bot with a dog robot on his back." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p> By most accounts, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/astro-bot-kotaku-review-playstation-5-1851640280&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/astro-bot-kotaku-review-playstation-5-1851640280"><em>Astro Bot</em></a></span>, the incredible PlayStation 5 platformer that pays a loving tribute to Sony’s (<span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/astro-bot-playstation-ps5-references-characters-1851640150&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/astro-bot-playstation-ps5-references-characters-1851640150">spotty</a></span>) gaming legacy, is a pretty straightforward game. Team Asobi has created an excellent experience that is able to communicate a lot without words or hand-holding. However, we do have some tips to hopefully mitigate what little frustration you might encounter while playing <em>Astro Bot</em>.. Here’s some advice as you head into this joyful, PlayStation-themed roller coaster ride. </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/astro-bot-tips-guides-collectibles-photo-mode-1851642300&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/astro-bot-tips-guides-collectibles-photo-mode-1851642300">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="85a908c8645db2fc66e673d3e97e93ec" data-recommend-id="image://85a908c8645db2fc66e673d3e97e93ec" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="740" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Astro stands on green grass in front of a yellow crane." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Astro stands on green grass in front of a yellow crane." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Sony / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="85a908c8645db2fc66e673d3e97e93ec" data-recommend-id="image://85a908c8645db2fc66e673d3e97e93ec" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="740" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Astro stands on green grass in front of a yellow crane." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p> The <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/astro-bot-kotaku-review-playstation-5-1851640280&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/astro-bot-kotaku-review-playstation-5-1851640280">utterly wonderful</a></span> Sony platformer <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/tag/astro-bot&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/tag/astro-bot"><em>Astro Bot</em></a></span> has two main collectables in each level: bots and puzzle pieces. However, some levels contain something else: secret exits that can only be found by completing very specific tasks, or snooping around in some extremely hidden locations that you may have otherwise overlooked. Yeah, there’s a whole load of more levels to find! </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/astro-bot-secret-exits-bonus-levels-guide-1851643005&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/astro-bot-secret-exits-bonus-levels-guide-1851643005">Read More</a></span></p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/games/astro-bot&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/games/astro-bot">You can find all our <em>Astro Bot</em> coverage here</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="d48b1a0cdf86b5e013f2fe9685c07fac" data-recommend-id="image://d48b1a0cdf86b5e013f2fe9685c07fac" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="740" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Balatro game in play, cards everywhere." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A Balatro game in play, cards everywhere." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->PlayStack</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="d48b1a0cdf86b5e013f2fe9685c07fac" data-recommend-id="image://d48b1a0cdf86b5e013f2fe9685c07fac" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="740" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A Balatro game in play, cards everywhere." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>  <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/biggest-poker-hold-em-pot-win-3-million-record-dwan-fei-1850492142&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/biggest-poker-hold-em-pot-win-3-million-record-dwan-fei-1850492142">Poker</a></span> isn’t the most exciting game to play alone. <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/poker-night-at-the-inventory-is-an-awkward-time-capsule-1830191319&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/poker-night-at-the-inventory-is-an-awkward-time-capsule-1830191319">Even against computer players</a></span> in a video game, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/poker-2022-cheat-adelstein-robbi-jade-lew-instagram-1849609027&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/poker-2022-cheat-adelstein-robbi-jade-lew-instagram-1849609027">poker</a></span> isn’t much fun. <em>Balatro</em>—out now on Xbox, PlayStation, Switch, and PC—understands this. Instead of playing other opponents and placing bets, this roguelike deck builder is all about making winning hands and collecting powerful cards to help you earn big combos. And also there’s some weird cosmic magic, too. Don’t worry about it. </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/balatro-poker-roguelike-worth-it-is-it-good-review-pc-1851283124&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/balatro-poker-roguelike-worth-it-is-it-good-review-pc-1851283124">Read More</a></span></p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/games/balatro&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/games/balatro">You can find all our <em>Balatro</em> coverage here</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="9b347437446762a60a86cdb8888a3f95" data-recommend-id="image://9b347437446762a60a86cdb8888a3f95" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="740" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Strohl, the protagonist, Gallica, and Hulkenburg look at the camera." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Strohl, the protagonist, Gallica, and Hulkenburg look at the camera." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Atlus / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="9b347437446762a60a86cdb8888a3f95" data-recommend-id="image://9b347437446762a60a86cdb8888a3f95" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="740" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Strohl, the protagonist, Gallica, and Hulkenburg look at the camera." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>  <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/metaphor-refantazio-review-pc-ps5-xbox-persona-atlus-1851665876&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/metaphor-refantazio-review-pc-ps5-xbox-persona-atlus-1851665876"><em>Metaphor: ReFantazio</em></a></span>, the new fantasy RPG from the minds behind <em>Persona</em>, is a pretty dense game. There are a lot of systems to keep track of, levels to grind, and time to manage as you travel through the world of Euchronia. It’s easy to get overwhelmed by all the things to do when actual in-game days pass when you so much as talk to someone. </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/metaphor-refantazio-tips-archetypes-followers-mp-items-1851670117&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/metaphor-refantazio-tips-archetypes-followers-mp-items-1851670117">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="7257c2eb6b0720524860a301ca47f626" data-recommend-id="image://7257c2eb6b0720524860a301ca47f626" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="739" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Zorba, looking all pretty in his purple outfit." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Zorba, looking all pretty in his purple outfit." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Atlus / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="7257c2eb6b0720524860a301ca47f626" data-recommend-id="image://7257c2eb6b0720524860a301ca47f626" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="739" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Zorba, looking all pretty in his purple outfit." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p> In retrospect, it is a little weird how that otherwise ridiculously generous multi-hour demo for <em>Metaphor: ReFantazio</em> just kinda decided, “You’ve had enough,” after a random boss in Regalith Grand Cathedral. Over a million people have since told Atlus, “<em>We’ll</em> tell <em>you</em> when we’ve had enough,” and bit the bullet on the full game. That’s excellent news for us JRPG sickos, but that demo might give you delusions that all the bosses are just random collections of minions. That is quickly dispelled when you hit the game’s first <em>real </em>challenge. </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/metaphor-refantazio-zorba-boss-how-to-beat-1851672980&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/metaphor-refantazio-zorba-boss-how-to-beat-1851672980">Read More</a></span></p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/games/metaphor-refantazio&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/games/metaphor-refantazio">You can find all our <em>Metaphor: ReFantazio</em> coverage here</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="7ee0223cb7d07cb1e5c37490d4dcc463" data-recommend-id="image://7ee0223cb7d07cb1e5c37490d4dcc463" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="740" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Senua looks past the camera with her face half-submerged in water." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Senua looks past the camera with her face half-submerged in water." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Ninja Theory / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="7ee0223cb7d07cb1e5c37490d4dcc463" data-recommend-id="image://7ee0223cb7d07cb1e5c37490d4dcc463" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="740" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Senua looks past the camera with her face half-submerged in water." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>  <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/senua-saga-hellblade-2-sacrifice-review-xbox-pc-1851489149&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/senua-saga-hellblade-2-sacrifice-review-xbox-pc-1851489149"><em>Senua’s Saga: Hellblade II</em></a></span>, <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/ninja-theory-hellblade-new-game-greenlit-microsoft-1851490677&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/ninja-theory-hellblade-new-game-greenlit-microsoft-1851490677">Ninja Theory’s</a></span> latest narrative action-adventure game, arrived on May 21, 2024 for Xbox and PC. While many may be divided over its simple combat and lengthy puzzles, there’s no denying that <em>Hellblade 2</em> is a visually stunning game, especially on a PC with the horsepower to push the game to near-photorealistic levels of detail. </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/hellblade-2-senuas-saga-combat-fire-1851493666&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/hellblade-2-senuas-saga-combat-fire-1851493666">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="4516328518ceb1623aa3444fcd290364" data-recommend-id="image://4516328518ceb1623aa3444fcd290364" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="740" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Senua holds an object as an offering." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Senua holds an object as an offering." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Ninja Theory / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="4516328518ceb1623aa3444fcd290364" data-recommend-id="image://4516328518ceb1623aa3444fcd290364" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="740" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Senua holds an object as an offering." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure></div><div><figure id="" data-id="d658c9f00ce17f1cc9d7a0b205641e83" data-recommend-id="image://d658c9f00ce17f1cc9d7a0b205641e83" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="740" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Part man, part monkey, the character from Chinese legend stands in fine armor." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Part man, part monkey, the character from Chinese legend stands in fine armor." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Game Science / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="d658c9f00ce17f1cc9d7a0b205641e83" data-recommend-id="image://d658c9f00ce17f1cc9d7a0b205641e83" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="740" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Part man, part monkey, the character from Chinese legend stands in fine armor." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>  <em>Black Myth: Wukong</em> features a wide variety of materials you’ll need to collect if you’re going to upgrade your weapons and armor. And trust me, you’re going to want to, as this game can be brutally difficult if your gear isn’t up to par. Early in the game, you’ll be able to start earning one such material known as Stone Spirits, which are required for upgrading certain weapon tiers. You’ll want to get your hands on plenty of these little stones, and we know just how. </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/black-myth-wukong-stone-spirits-farming-guide-1851660978&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/black-myth-wukong-stone-spirits-farming-guide-1851660978">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="19578fef8bb9c6ef705490248bb6f70f" data-recommend-id="image://19578fef8bb9c6ef705490248bb6f70f" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="740" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A man stands in front of a burning building, viewed through a giant arch." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A man stands in front of a burning building, viewed through a giant arch." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="fair-use" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Game Science / Kotaku</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="19578fef8bb9c6ef705490248bb6f70f" data-recommend-id="image://19578fef8bb9c6ef705490248bb6f70f" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="740" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A man stands in front of a burning building, viewed through a giant arch." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>  <em>Black Myth: Wukong</em> is a lengthy and challenging game filled with over 80 bosses and tons of enemy types to tackle, promising that you’ll need to put your skills to the test if you want to see it through to one of its multiple endings. The opening hours of the game give you a lot to learn and think about, and getting to grips with how the game’s various mechanics work can take a little getting used to. As such, we’ve compiled a list of early game tips here that we hope will aid you in the opening hours of <em>Black Myth: Wukong</em>. </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/black-myth-wukong-guides-and-walkthroughs-1851630887/slides/6&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/black-myth-wukong-guides-and-walkthroughs-1851630887/slides/6">Read More</a></span></p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/games/black-myth-wukong&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/games/black-myth-wukong">You can read all our <em>Black Myth: Wukong</em> coverage here</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="07bb2b9f36b0591ada226b954dc6ff2f" data-recommend-id="image://07bb2b9f36b0591ada226b954dc6ff2f" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="740" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Helldivers shoot at an alien bug." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="Helldivers shoot at an alien bug." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Arrowhead Game Studios</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="07bb2b9f36b0591ada226b954dc6ff2f" data-recommend-id="image://07bb2b9f36b0591ada226b954dc6ff2f" data-format="jpg" data-width="1315" data-height="740" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="Helldivers shoot at an alien bug." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p> Third-person cooperative shooter <em>Helldivers 2</em> recently landed on PC and PS5. Featuring intense, chaotic gun fights against alien threats across the galaxy it’s proven <span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/helldivers-2-server-down-status-ps5-pc-steam-1851248827&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/helldivers-2-server-down-status-ps5-pc-steam-1851248827">pretty popular</a></span>—so much so that you might be struggling to get into a match right now due to server load. Assuming you can get into one, I’ve rounded up a number of essential settings tucked into the game’s options that might make for a better experience. </p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/helldivers-2-settings-aim-anti-aliasing-ps5-pc-tips-1851252612&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/helldivers-2-settings-aim-anti-aliasing-ps5-pc-tips-1851252612">Read More</a></span></p></div></div><div><figure id="" data-id="c68acfdd15aba27ae465693ef61962e4" data-recommend-id="image://c68acfdd15aba27ae465693ef61962e4" data-format="jpg" data-width="1600" data-height="900" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A large explosion in the middle of a battlefield, our soldier front and center." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false" contenteditable="false" draggable="false"><div contenteditable="false" data-alt="A large explosion in the middle of a battlefield, our soldier front and center." data-link-reference="" data-link-target="" data-syndicationrights="true" data-imagerights="other-license" data-hide="false" data-hidecredit="false"><p><figcaption>Screenshot<!-- -->: <!-- -->Arrowhead Game Studios</figcaption></p></div><span data-id="c68acfdd15aba27ae465693ef61962e4" data-recommend-id="image://c68acfdd15aba27ae465693ef61962e4" data-format="jpg" data-width="1600" data-height="900" data-lightbox="false" data-alt="A large explosion in the middle of a battlefield, our soldier front and center." data-recommended="false" data-hide="false"></span></figure><div><p>Whether you’re fighting bugs or bots, you need the right tools for the job. As <em>Helldivers 2 </em>finishes its 60-day roadmap and releases the new patch, there’s no better time to visit Super Earth’s armories and take your pick of the litter.<br></p><p>If you want to save the citizens of Super Earth, you need to take advantage of the tools available. These are the best weapons in <em>Helldivers 2</em> currently, with a mix of Stratagems and primary and secondary weapons for a well-rounded arsenal to choose from!</p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/helldivers-2-best-weapons-1851675209&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/helldivers-2-best-weapons-1851675209">Read More</a></span></p><p><span><a data-ga="[[&quot;Embedded Url&quot;,&quot;Internal link&quot;,&quot;https://kotaku.com/games/helldivers-2&quot;,{&quot;metric25&quot;:1}]]" href="https://kotaku.com/games/helldivers-2">You can read all our <em>Helldivers II</em> coverage here</a></span></p><p>.</p></div></div></div></div>]]></content:encoded>
